==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[dissuadere]]'' (to advise against, to oppose by argument), from ''[[dis-]]'' (against), + ''[[suadere]]'' (to urge).

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪd|-eɪd]]

====Verb====
'''to dissuade''' ('''dissuades''', '''dissuaded''', '''dissuading''')
#To [[convince]] not to try or do
